{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_spring_mornings/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Woken by earlier born sun,<br>\nChills harmless as nettles while young,<br>\nThere's frost but winter's on the run,<br>\nColour nigh seems it don't belong,<br>\nOn battle worn ground life will win,<br>\nMother nature is now yawning,<br>\nMemories bound with breaths breathed in,<br>\nThe promise of a spring morning,<br>\nGrowth sprouts from the canvas wiped clean,<br>\nWoods ready for chaos filled scenes,<br>\nLife's waiting in dashes of green,<br>\nBlessings are spoken by May queens,<br>\nA mist veils the earnest beauty,<br>\nWe see clear once the sun clips trees,<br>\nFauna want for patience like we,<br>\nThese months forever play the tease.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 22, 2020","title":"Spring Mornings","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/450ea96d33f40bf2df9220d9f7b4afe2/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 22 Spring Mornings.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/251f09c5ea36ce8a755070b279a72579/3c17d/poem%20spring%20mornings.png","srcSet":"/static/251f09c5ea36ce8a755070b279a72579/69585/poem%20spring%20mornings.png 200w,\n/static/251f09c5ea36ce8a755070b279a72579/497c6/poem%20spring%20mornings.png 400w,\n/static/251f09c5ea36ce8a755070b279a72579/3c17d/poem%20spring%20mornings.png 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_spring_mornings/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}